post_cb({"486508": {"CommentCount": "2", "ViewCount": "420", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "14444", "CreationDate": "2009-01-28T04:44:45.520", "LastActivityDate": "2009-03-22T22:08:30.110", "AnswerCount": "1", "LastEditDate": "2009-03-22T22:08:30.110", "AcceptedAnswerId": "486597", "LastEditorDisplayName": "moocha", "Title": "How does template argument shadowing work in VS2005?", "Id": "486508", "Score": "4", "Body": "<p>In GCC this code won't compile, because T gets shadowed, however in VS2005 it compiles with no warnings, so what are the assumptions VS compiler is making?</p>\n<pre><code>template&lt;typename T&gt;\nclass Foo\n{\n    template&lt;typename T&gt;\n    void Bar(const T&amp; bar)\n    {\n      ...\n    }\n};\n</code></pre>\n", "Tags": "<c++><templates><gcc><visual-studio-2005>", "OwnerUserId": "15124", "OwnerDisplayName": "Robert Gould"}, "486597": {"CommentCount": "1", "CreationDate": "2009-01-28T05:52:59.097", "LastEditorUserId": "34509", "LastActivityDate": "2009-03-21T05:42:13.267", "ParentId": "486508", "PostTypeId": "2", "LastEditorDisplayName": "litb", "LastEditDate": "2009-03-21T05:42:13.267", "Id": "486597", "Score": "7", "Body": "<p>Found the right answer after 3 months of searching :) It's in <code>14.6.1/4</code> of the Standard:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_486508_486597_0\">A template-parameter shall not be redeclared within its scope (including nested scopes). A template-parameter shall not have the same name as the template name. </p>\n<p id=\"so_486508_486597_1\">Example:</p>\n<pre><code>template&lt;class T, int i&gt; class Y {\n    int T;\n    // error: template-parameter redeclared\n    void f() {\n        char T;\n        // error: template-parameter redeclared\n    }\n};\n\ntemplate&lt;class X&gt; class X; // error: template-parameter redeclared\n</code></pre>\n</blockquote>\n<p>If the Microsoft compiler let it compile without errors or even warnings, it is not conforming. I don't know what could drive it to allow it without moaning. You could try to high warning levels. </p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "34509", "OwnerDisplayName": "litb"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_486508_486597_0": {"section_id": 184, "quality": 1.0, "length": 14}}, "n3337": {"so_486508_486597_0": {"section_id": 178, "quality": 1.0, "length": 14}}, "n4659": {"so_486508_486597_0": {"section_id": 189, "quality": 1.0, "length": 14}}}});